1. Go the ./README.md file and understand how the project works
2. Then according to the type of functionality review the ./README_DEV_FRONT.md, ./README_DEV_BACK.md or both to now more about the programming guidelines.
3. Ask the user what must be tested and how the tests must look, wait for their response.
4. Build the components according to the tests following the guidelines.
5. Implement the functionalities.
6. Refresh the README.md, ./README_FRONT.md and ./README_BACK.md with the new feature implemented
